11.4 The Receiving Party acknowledges that Confidential Information, for the purposes of this Agreement, encompasses any data or knowledge not falling under the following exceptions:

(i) Information obtained by the Receiving Party from a source other than the Disclosing Party, and without any breach of this Agreement;

(ii) Information that becomes publicly accessible through means other than an unauthorized disclosure by the Disclosing Party or its representatives;

(iii) Information independently developed by the Receiving Party without using any Confidential Information obtained from the Disclosing Party;

(iv) Information for which the Receiving Party is legally compelled to disclose, such as under a judicial order, regulatory requirement, or statutory provision. However, the Receiving Party shall make reasonable efforts to provide written notice to the Disclosing Party prior to any disclosure, allowing the Disclosing Party an opportunity to seek appropriate remedies;

(v) Information that is already owned by the Disclosing Party under this Agreement or has been previously disclosed on a non-confidential basis under the terms of this Agreement.
